text: thumb Françoise Branget (born 8 August 1953 in Chalon-sur-Saône, Saône-et- Loire) was the deputy representing Doubs's 1st constituency of the National Assembly of France. She was a member of the Union for a Popular Movement. ==References== Category:1953 births Category:Living people Category:People from Chalon-sur-Saône Category:Union for a Popular Movement politicians Category:Women members of the National Assembly (France) Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:21st-century French women politicians
title: Françoise Branget
